<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Tab Fridge – Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Effective date: <strong>2026-02-24</strong></p>
  </header>

  <main>
    <div class="note">
      <strong>Summary:</strong> Tab Fridge stores your saved tabs and reminders locally on your device.
      It does not send your data to any external servers, does not sell data, and does not use tracking or analytics.
    </div>

    <h2>1. What Tab Fridge does</h2>
    <p>
      Tab Fridge lets you save (“freeze”) the current browser tab with an optional note and a reminder time.
      When the reminder is due, the extension can show a notification so you can reopen the tab.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information the extension processes</h2>
    <p>Tab Fridge processes only the information needed to provide its functionality. This may include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Frozen tab details:</strong> tab URL and page title.</li>
      <li><strong>User-provided content:</strong> labels and notes you type into the extension.</li>
      <li><strong>Optional selected text:</strong> if you enable “save selection”, the extension may store the text you highlighted on the page.</li>
      <li><strong>Reminder metadata:</strong> reminder date/time and item status (e.g., pending/due/opened).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Where your data is stored</h2>
    <p>
      All data is stored <strong>locally on your device</strong> using <code>chrome.storage.local</code>.
      Tab Fridge does <strong>not</strong> transmit your data to the developer or to any third-party servers.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Permissions and why they are needed</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><code>storage</code>: to save frozen items locally so they persist across sessions.</li>
      <li><code>alarms</code>: to schedule reminders at the time you choose.</li>
      <li><code>notifications</code>: to show reminders and quick actions (Open / Snooze).</li>
      <li><code>activeTab</code>: to access the current tab details only when you click the extension.</li>
      <li><code>scripting</code>: to read page title/URL and optional selected text only on your request.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Tab Fridge does not request any host permissions and does not automatically run on websites in the background.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Data sharing</h2>
    <p>
      Tab Fridge does not share, sell, or rent your data to third parties.
      The extension does not use analytics, advertising, or tracking services.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data retention and deletion</h2>
    <p>
      Data is kept on your device until you delete it.
      You can remove individual items from the list or clear all items using the extension interface.
      Uninstalling the extension also removes its locally stored data.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Security</h2>
    <p>
      The extension stores data locally and does not transmit it over the network.
      However, no method of storage is 100% secure; you should avoid saving sensitive information in notes or selections.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Children’s privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Tab Fridge is not intended for children under 13 and does not knowingly collect personal information from children.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy changes, the updated version will be published at the same URL with a new effective date.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have questions about this policy, contact: <strong>YOUR_CONTACT_EMAIL</strong>
    </p>

    <footer>
      <p>Tab Fridge – Privacy Policy</p>
    </footer>
  </main>
